      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_task_1ae16435f5e0d15e4e569eec7da8de5f65" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void create</definition>
        <argsstring>(k_thread_stack_t *stack, size_t stack_size, int prio)</argsstring>
        <name>create</name>
        <param>
          <type>k_thread_stack_t *</type>
          <declname>stack</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>size_t</type>
          <declname>stack_size</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>prio</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to create a task and to assign the name of the task. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>stack</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to stack object of type k_thread_stack_t </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>stack_size</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Size of the stack in bytes </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>prio</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The priority of the task</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
This function create a task, assign the stack and the priority and return the unique ID of the task provided by the OS of type k_tid_t and the thread administration structure thread_handle of type struct k_thread by calling the function k_thread_create provided by the operating system. Afterwars the task&apos;s name will be assigned by calling function k_thread_name_set also provided by the operating system. <linebreak/>
Priority: The smaller the value, the higher the priority </para>
        </detaileddescription>
