    <briefdescription>
<para>RTOS wrapper for multithreading support. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The task class implements a C++ wrapper of the thread API provided by the Zephyr operating system. See details in Zephyr <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/services/threads/index.html">thread documentation</ulink> or in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__thread__apis.html">API documentation</ulink>. The task class is the base class of all task in the AXO track system. All tasks shall be derived from this base class. Every task has it&apos;s own stack, which needs to be created outside of the task and an assigned priority. The task class provides a method to create and to start the task and to assign an unique ID. It provides a virtual task function, which needs to be implemented in the derived classes and shall implements the endless loop. Furthermore it provides the entry point for the operating system, which simply calls the task function. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
